Cameron Says ‘Of Course Inflation Is Too High’ in Britain

-- B y   G o n z a l o   V i n a
-- 
2011-10-19T11:17:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-19/cameron-says-of-course-inflation-is-too-high-in-britain.html
Prime Minister  David Cameron  said
U.K. inflation is too rapid, blaming rises in food and energy
prices, a fall in the value of the pound and an increase in
sales tax.  “Of course inflation is too high,” he told lawmakers in
Parliament in  London  today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Gonzalo Vina in London at 
 gvina@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
